Ok, I was a little lax about what I said.  Iteration is only done if
it is requested.  You were correct for the case of non-recursive queries.
But nslookup doesn't print the ttl.  If you look, the ttl on each of
those RR's was 0.  You can't corrupt a cache much with that ttl and 
it only sends back the NS RR's, and not the A RR's.

					Jim

